deja (0.2.0) noble; urgency=medium

  * GUI overhaul: search moves into the header bar, card-style list,
    proper empty state, native GNOME styling via libadwaita when present.
  * Single click now only selects; Enter or double-click copies and
    closes (pinning after a click no longer fights the window).
  * New selection mode (Ctrl+S or header toggle): checkboxes plus an
    action bar for bulk pin/unpin/delete; Ctrl+A selects all.
  * Type-anywhere search (keystrokes route to the search field).

 -- Ibuchukwu <ibumeano@gmail.com>  Sat, 04 Jul 2026 12:00:00 +0100

deja (0.1.1) noble; urgency=medium

  * Fix the flashing "unknown" window on GNOME: never poll with wl-paste
    on Wayland (each read opened a transient focus-stealing window on
    compositors without the data-control protocol).
  * New native Wayland data-control watcher (ext-data-control-v1 and
    zwlr_data_control_v1) — event-driven and windowless on Sway, KDE,
    and other compositors that ship the protocol; no wl-clipboard needed.
  * New XWayland-bridge watcher for GNOME: event-driven via GDK/XFixes
    on the X11 clipboard, which Mutter mirrors in both directions.
  * The daemon now serves a control socket; `deja copy` and the GUI set
    the clipboard through it (windowless, and content survives exit).
  * External clipboard tools demoted to optional fallbacks
    (Recommends: wl-clipboard, Suggests: xclip).

 -- Ibuchukwu <ibumeano@gmail.com>  Sat, 04 Jul 2026 10:30:00 +0100

deja (0.1.0) noble; urgency=medium

  * Initial release.
  * Clipboard daemon: event-driven on Wayland (wl-paste --watch) with
    automatic polling fallback on X11 / older compositors.
  * SQLite + FTS5 storage with dedupe, pinning, pruning, and purge.
  * CLI: list, find, show, copy, pin, rm, purge, pause/resume, status.
  * GTK4 search popup (deja gui).
  * systemd user service and optional GNOME hotkey via deja setup.
  * Password-manager clipboard hints are never recorded.

 -- Ibuchukwu <ibumeano@gmail.com>  Sat, 04 Jul 2026 09:00:00 +0100
